{
  "stem": "5810.1",
  "chunk_idx": 7,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And I understand that these hats went to the Russian front.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "They were warm hats.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "They went to Russia front for the Germans.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And that the deal made was you manufactured this, you live one more day, so does your family.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "And I'm convinced now, and I have to live with the fact that a lot of people made certain deals, just to survive another day.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "But I guess it wasn't understood that way by the underground and the Belgians.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "And because all they could see is that he was helping the Germans in some way, he was called a collaborator, and they decided to kill him.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "And so now I know that my father was killed by the Belgian underground, possibly even the Jewish Belgian underground.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "And [SIGHS] I-- I have mixed feelings about it.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "But I have to tell myself that he did the right thing for his family.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, things became, at that point, untenable.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And we saw the convoys starting to come, the Germans coming with trucks, rounding up Jews all over the neighborhoods, putting them in trucks, and taking them away.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And we started to hear stories about-- not necessarily yet concentration camps, but the Jews that were taken never came back.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And in those times, we believed that they were taken to work camps and so on.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "That's what was explained to us.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And this is what we read, I suppose, in newspapers or heard on radios.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "But we-- we knew that we had to get away from there.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So the-- the underground was quite active in those days, and the Jewish underground even more so, in trying to help and hide Jews, and also to get them away from the country.",
      "word_count": 33
    }
  ],
